<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="538" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,836,1367]" box="[151,829,836,863]" pageId="15" pageNumber="538">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,829,836,863]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" reason="1">
<taxonomicName authority="(Carter, 1885 a) sensu Dendy (1924)" authorityName="sensu Dendy" authorityYear="1924" baseAuthorityName="Carter" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[151,829,836,863]" class="Demospongiae" family="Dysideidae" genus="Dysidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dictyoceratida" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="hirciniformis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,829,836,863]" pageId="15" pageNumber="538">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,402,836,863]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="538">Dysidea hirciniformis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Carter, H. J." box="[417,582,836,863]" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" pagination="196 - 222" refId="ref9958" refString="Carter, H. J. (1885 a) Descriptions of sponges from the neighbourhood of Port Phillip Heads, South Australia. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 5, 15 (87), 196 - 222. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222938509459319" type="journal article" year="1885">Carter, 1885a</bibRefCitation>
) 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[597,662,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="538">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dendy, A." box="[670,829,836,863]" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" pagination="269 - 392" refId="ref10439" refString="Dendy, A. (1924) Porifera. Part I. Non-Antarctic sponges. Natural history report. British Antarctic (Terra Nova) Expedition, 1910, Zoology, 6 (3), 269 - 392, pls. I-XV." type="journal article" year="1924">Dendy (1924)</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,836,1367]" pageId="15" pageNumber="538">
<bibRefCitation author="Dendy, A." box="[151,307,873,899]" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" pagination="269 - 392" refId="ref10439" refString="Dendy, A. (1924) Porifera. Part I. Non-Antarctic sponges. Natural history report. British Antarctic (Terra Nova) Expedition, 1910, Zoology, 6 (3), 269 - 392, pls. I-XV." type="journal article" year="1924">Dendy (1924)</bibRefCitation>
considered his highly characteristic, thin, ramose, deep subtidal North Cape specimens, to be similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Dendy" authorityYear="1924" baseAuthorityName="Carter" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[180,423,909,935]" class="Demospongiae" family="Dysideidae" genus="Dysidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dictyoceratida" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="hirciniformis">
<emphasis box="[180,423,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="538">Dysidea hirciniformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from Port Phillip Heads, 
<collectingRegion box="[717,894,909,935]" country="Australia" name="South Australia" pageId="15" pageNumber="538">South Australia</collectingRegion>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lendenfeld, R. V." box="[904,1113,909,935]" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref11149" refString="Lendenfeld, R. V. (1889) A Monograph of the horny sponges. Trubner and Co., London, 936 + 3 (iii-iv), pls. 1 - 50." type="journal article" year="1889">Lendenfeld (1889)</bibRefCitation>
described them as forming a bunch of cylindrical, digitate, upright branches, about 
<quantity box="[757,836,944,971]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
thick, 
<quantity box="[912,1005,944,971]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" unit="mm" value="150.0">150 mm</quantity>
long, with a conulose surface, conules being 
<quantity box="[222,310,980,1007]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
high and the same distance apart, with rare oscules, 
<quantity box="[915,1009,981,1007]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
diameter. The colour in life was pale buff with purple tips and the fibres were packed with sand-grains, the primary fibres 
<quantity box="[1091,1177,1017,1043]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" unit="mm" value="180.0">180 µm</quantity>
thick, secondary fibres 
<quantity box="[151,280,1052,1079]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" unit="mm" value="115.0" valueMax="150.0" valueMin="80.0">80–150 µm</quantity>
thick, forming a mesh about 
<quantity box="[609,682,1053,1079]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" unit="mm" value="80.0">80 µm</quantity>
wide (
<bibRefCitation author="Lendenfeld, R. V." box="[758,1011,1052,1079]" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref11149" refString="Lendenfeld, R. V. (1889) A Monograph of the horny sponges. Trubner and Co., London, 936 + 3 (iii-iv), pls. 1 - 50." type="journal article" year="1889">Lendenfeld 1889: 665</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="538" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,836,1367]" pageId="15" pageNumber="538">
Without histological examination of the original specimens and comparison with Dendy’s material, it is impossible to say with certainty whether the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Dendy" authorityYear="1924" baseAuthorityName="Carter" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[671,816,1125,1151]" class="Demospongiae" family="Dysideidae" genus="Dysidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dictyoceratida" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="hirciniformis">
<emphasis box="[671,816,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="538">hirciniformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is valid for the North Cape specimens: 
<bibRefCitation author="Dendy, A." pageId="15" pageNumber="538" pagination="269 - 392" refId="ref10439" refString="Dendy, A. (1924) Porifera. Part I. Non-Antarctic sponges. Natural history report. British Antarctic (Terra Nova) Expedition, 1910, Zoology, 6 (3), 269 - 392, pls. I-XV." type="journal article" year="1924">Dendy (1924: 384)</bibRefCitation>
indicated that there were differences. Despite the disjunct distribution, the likelihood of conspecificity of North Cape specimens with a South Australian species is moderate, as there are several clear precedents including 
<taxonomicName authority="Carter, 1886" authorityName="Carter" authorityYear="1886" box="[151,569,1233,1259]" class="Demospongiae" family="Polymastiidae" genus="Polymastia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="massalis">
<emphasis box="[151,277,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="538">Polymastia</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[324,420,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="538">massalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Carter, H. J." box="[429,569,1233,1259]" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" pagination="119 - 121" refId="ref10064" refString="Carter, H. J. (1886) Descriptions of sponges from the neighbourhood of Port Phillip Heads, South Australia. Annals and magazines of natural history, 5, 119 - 121. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222938609460109" type="journal article" year="1886">Carter, 1886</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation author="Kelly-Borges, M. &amp; Bergquist, P. R." box="[618,985,1233,1259]" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" pagination="367 - 402" refId="ref10755" refString="Kelly-Borges, M. &amp; Bergquist, P. R. (1997) Revision of Southwest Pacific Polymastiidae (Porifera: Demospongiae: Hadromerida) with descriptions of new species of Polymastia Bowerbank, Tylexocladus Topsent, and Acanthopolymastia gen. nov. from New Zealand and the Norfolk Ridge, New Caledonia. New Zealand Journal of Marine and Freshwater Research, 31 (3), 367 - 402. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00288330.1997.9516772" type="journal article" year="1997">Kelly-Borges &amp; Bergquist 1997</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Hooper in Hooper &amp; Wiedenmayer, 1994" authorityName="Hooper in Hooper &amp; Wiedenmayer" authorityYear="1994" class="Demospongiae" family="Tethyidae" genus="Tethya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="bergquistae">
<emphasis box="[1006,1220,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="538">Tethya bergquistae</emphasis>
Hooper in 
<bibRefCitation author="Hooper, J. N. A. &amp; Wiedenmayer, F." pageId="15" pageNumber="538" pagination="1 - 620" refId="ref10660" refString="Hooper, J. N. A. &amp; Wiedenmayer, F. (1994) Porifera. In: Wells, A. (Ed.), Zoological Catalogue of Australia. Vol. 12. CSIRO, Melbourne, pp. 1 - 620." type="book chapter" year="1994">Hooper &amp; Wiedenmayer, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation author="Bergquist, P. R. &amp; Kelly-Borges, M." box="[462,832,1269,1295]" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" pagination="37 - 72" refId="ref9699" refString="Bergquist, P. R. &amp; Kelly-Borges, M. (1991) An evaluation of the genus Tethya (Porifera: Demospongiae: Hadromerida) with descriptions of new species from the Southwest Pacific. The Beagle, Records of the Northern Territory Museum of Arts and Sciences, 8 (1), 37 - 72." type="journal article" year="1991">Bergquist &amp; Kelly-Borges 1991</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bowerbank, 1841)" baseAuthorityName="Bowerbank" baseAuthorityYear="1841" box="[906,1350,1269,1295]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chondropsidae" genus="Chondropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="kirkii">
<emphasis box="[906,1117,1269,1295]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="538">Chondropsis kirkii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bowerbank, J. S." box="[1135,1342,1269,1295]" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" pagination="161 - 162" refId="ref9811" refString="Bowerbank, J. S. (1841) Descriptions of three species of sponge, containing some new forms of organization. Microscopical Journal London, 1, 161 - 162. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2818.1841. tb 06423. x" type="journal article" year="1841">Bowerbank, 1841</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Carter, 1885 b)" baseAuthorityName="Carter" baseAuthorityYear="1885" class="Demospongiae" family="Crellidae" genus="Crella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="incrustans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="538">Crella incrustans</emphasis>
